# Friday Rules for Virtual Guestbook Project

## Code Base Architecture

- /client - Next.js TypeScript frontend
  - /client/src/components - React components for the guestbook UI
  - /client/src/icons - SVG icon components contributed by users
  - /client/src/data - Contains guestbook.json for data storage
  - /client/pages - Next.js page components

## Development Setup

- Client: `cd client && npm install && npm run dev` (runs on default Next.js port)

## Testing Guidelines

- No explicit testing configuration is currently set up in the project
- To add tests, consider using Jest and React Testing Library with Next.js

## Linting Guidelines

- Client: Uses ESLint with next/core-web-vitals configuration
  - Configuration in client/package.json under "eslintConfig"
  - Run linting with `cd client && npx eslint .`

## Build and Deployment

- Build: `cd client && npm run build`
- Start: `cd client && npm start` (runs on port 3002)
